HUNDREDS of Balobedu joined their seventh Rain Queen, Mosalanabo Modjadji (13) to officially celebrate the return of the Modjadji queenship on Saturday.President Cyril Ramaphosa, former president Jacob Zuma, Minister for Traditional Affairs Zweli Mkhize, Limpopo Premier Stan Mathaba, Vha-Venda King Mphephu Ramabulana and others joined the Balozwi to help celebrate the recognition of her queenship.The Modjadji queenship was restored in March 2016 after the previous government downgraded the power of the Rain Queen, Makoma Modjadji, in 1972 to that of a chieftain.if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");var viewReq = new Array();function vu(u) {var i=new Image();i.src=u.replace("&amp;","&");viewReq.push(i);}vu("https://securepubads.g.doubleclick.net/pcs/view?xai\x3dAKAOjssW43vBIeUMWIKOYbCphH78ZktzgG04gkW_CDYGti0FvPDG4cioOtJEx84P38cMqkkYyH4CBkXRpEDbJcC8ETWanrN8kyS4HxIZRm6pdqnsWRzgbx0Cn1k7K8CBO7TQPaB2UZj7EfPXJFUK2gbK6gqPE6W6RoLSoCsLCWbSsrOAqrdg-Y1k0YVQZsyVd7Fyx-4BUuuJhyhmm0qX_vfswLt0mw4LyGSUy_qiMP53MGAE61uQXjrV2Wob0FQs2XodBitBTPLNQqQyuZWGkTMoi-vvmszD060\x26sig\x3dCg0ArKJSzJk4H_LVCFc0EAE\x26urlfix\x3d1\x26adurl\x3d")

   
